                  </persName>
            . On the 21st of December I was in Holborn. The two prisoners passed me. I followed them to the prosecutor's shop; they stopped twenty yards off the prosecutor's house, and had some conversation together. The young one went into the prosecutor's shop; the old woman made up to the print at the door; she drawed the print from where it was placed, and put it underneath her cloak. I let her come away about forty yards from the prosecutor's door, and then I took her. I asked her what she had got; she said nothing; I said, yes you have, under your cloak, and took it from her. I took her and the print into the prosecutor's shop; I shewed 
